oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Pete Seeger singing and telling stories
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Pete Seeger singing/telling stories "Which Side Are You On," "Winnsboro Cotton Mill Blues" recorded at Highlander Folk School.
Pete Seeger was a folk singer and social activist. He is best known for his protest songs in support of civil rights, workers rights, and environmental causes. Seeger died in 2014.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Folk music; Highlander Folk School (Monteagle, Tenn.); Seeger, Pete, 1919-2014
